Support USD coordSys (UsdShadeCoordSysAPI) bindings for MaterialX shaders

Verifies that a MaterialX ND_position_vector3 node with a custom `space`
input referencing a USD coordSys binding picks up the bound Xform's world
matrix and outputs positions in that frame. The conversion is applied via
an inserted arnold matrix_multiply_vector helper (see
libs/common/materials_utils.cpp).

In this scene a sphere at the origin is shaded by a standard_surface whose
base_color is driven by the world-space position seen through a coordSys
named "shifted" that is translated by (-0.5, 0, 0). The rendered sphere
therefore shows an asymmetric red gradient that would be symmetric without
the coordSys conversion.

PARAMS: {'scene':'test.usda'}
